{{Refimprove|date=November 2015}}
{{Soviet Union sidebar}}
The '''Inter-Regional Deputies' Group''' ({{lang-ru|Межрегиональная депутатская группа, МДГ}}) was the first legal parliamentary opposition in the [[Soviet Union]], a fraction formed in 1989 within the 1st [[Congress of People's Deputies of the Soviet Union|Congress of People's Deputies]]. It was the base of the formation of the [[Democratic Russia|Democratic Russia Election Bloc]] whose main political goal, suggested by [[Andrei Sakharov]], was to remove the [[Communist Party of the Soviet Union|Communist Party]] from power, in particular to remove the declaration of its leading role from the [[Constitution of the Soviet Union|constitution]]. The Inter-Regional Group operated until 1991. It was dissolved due to lack of the common constructive programme.<ref>[http://www.sovsekretno.ru/articles/id/2437/ Вся власть – Моссовету!], Leonid Velekhov's interview with [[Gavriil Kharitonovich Popov|Gavriil Popov]], "Совершенно секретно", No.3/250</ref>

