'''Loser.com''' is a [[domain name]] which existed as a [[URL redirect]] to several different webpages during most of its existence. {{As of|April 2018}}, it is a news website that publishes articles opposing [[Donald Trump]].
==History== The Loser.com domain name was registered in 1995 by Brian Connelly.<ref name="DailyBeast"/>
It redirected to the website of the [[Al Gore presidential campaign, 2000|2000 presidential campaign of Al Gore]] in 2000; a website opposing former [[Governor of South Carolina]] [[Jim Hodges]] in much of 2002; the [[Barack Obama presidential campaign, 2008|2008 presidential campaign of Barack Obama]] in 2008;{{efn-ua|“That wasn’t against Obama’s election!” Connelly said. “That was just getting people to register."<ref name="snopes">{{Cite web |url=http://www.snopes.com/2016/02/02/loser-com-donald-trump/ |title=Loser.com Redirects to Wikipedia Page for Donald Trump: Online nose-thumbing takes place after Trump's second-place finish in the Iowa caucuses. |last=Mikkelson |first=David |authorlink=David Mikkelson |date=May 4, 2016 |publisher=[[Snopes.com]] |access-date=April 5, 2017}}</ref>}} [[WikiLeaks]] in 2010; an article about American politician [[Sean Duffy]] in 2011; and the [[Reddit]] website in 2012.<ref name="DailyBeast">{{Cite web |url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2015/03/04/meet-kanye-west-s-no-1-online-troll-loser-com-owner-brian-connelly-on-shaming-kanye.html |title=Meet Kanye West’s No. 1 Online Troll: Loser.com Owner Brian Connelly on Shaming Kanye |last=Stern |first=Marlow |date=5 March 2015 |work=[[The Daily Beast]] |accessdate=April 5, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-intersect/wp/2015/03/03/a-short-history-of-loser-com-the-internets-best-troll/ |title=A short history of Loser.com, the Internet’s best troll |last=Dewey |first=Caitlin |date=3 March 2015 |work=[[The Washington Post]] |accessdate=April 5, 2017}}</ref> According to Connelly, the website sometimes redirects to topics he considers positive to increase their traffic.<ref name="DailyBeast" />
The domain name gained mainstream coverage in March 2015, when it redirected to the [[English Wikipedia]] entry for American rapper [[Kanye West]]; Marlow Stern of ''[[The Daily Beast]]'' suggested that the redirect was done in response to West's reactions to American singer [[Beck]]'s album ''[[Morning Phase]]'' winning [[Grammy Award for Album of the Year|Album of the Year]] at the [[57th Annual Grammy Awards]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2015/03/01/the-internet-is-trolling-kanye-west-loser-com-redirects-to-kanye-s-wikipedia-page.html |title=The Internet Is Trolling Kanye West: Loser.com Redirects to Kanye’s Wikipedia Page |last=Stern |first=Marlow |date=1 March 2015 |work=[[The Daily Beast]]}}</ref> Ryan Gajewski of ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' and Christopher Hooton of ''[[The Independent]]'' both suggested that the domain name was a Beck reference because "[[Loser (Beck song)|Loser]]" is one of Beck's most notable songs.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/losercom-redirects-kanye-wests-wikipedia-778827 |title=Loser.com Redirects to Kanye West's Wikipedia Page |last=Gajewski |first=Ryan |date=2 March 2015 |newspaper=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |accessdate=April 5, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/someone-made-losercom-redirect-to-kanye-wests-wikipedia-page-10079452.html |title=Someone made Loser.com redirect to Kanye West's Wikipedia page |last=Hooton |first=Christopher |date=2 March 2015 |newspaper=[[The Independent]] |accessdate=April 5, 2017}}</ref> In an interview with Stern on 5 March, Connelly admitted that he had a negative impression of West, and intended the redirection as a [[Internet trolling|troll]] attempt on the rapper.<ref name="DailyBeast" />
In February 2016, the website redirected to the English Wikipedia entry for then-[[United States presidential election, 2016|U.S. presidential candidate]] [[Donald Trump]] after he placed second in the [[United States presidential election in Iowa, 2016|Iowa caucus]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://time.com/4204929/donald-trump-trolled-loser-wikipedia/ |title=Loser.com Now Redirects to Donald Trump's Wikipedia Page |last=White |first=Daniel |date=2 February 2016 |work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]] |accessdate=April 5, 2017}}</ref> Defending the move, Connelly described Trump as "a man who attacks Muslims, who attacks Muslim Americans, who pushes fear and doubt" and "the definition of a loser".<ref name="WaPo2016">{{Cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-intersect/wp/2016/02/02/man-behind-the-updated-loser-com-donald-trump-is-the-definition-of-a-loser/ |title=Man behind the updated Loser.com: Donald Trump ‘is the definition of a loser’ |last=Dewey |first=Caitlin |date=2 February 2016 |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |accessdate=April 5, 2017}}</ref> {{As of|April 2017}}, loser.com is a news website that publishes articles opposing now-US President Trump.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://loser.com/ |title=Loser - The Donald Trump News Site |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6pUhcX6PX?url=http://loser.com/ |archive-date=5 April 2017 |dead-url=no |access-date=5 April 2017 |df= }}</ref>
When asked about his motives with his redirects, Connelly said the year 2000 redirect to losing Tennessee gubernatorial candidate Bill Daley's website was because “I think he was anti-gay”. He had "no comment" about the 2002 redirect to an opposition site targeting South Carolina Governor [[Jim Hodges]].<ref name="snopes" />
