'''No Limits Film Festival''' is an international student [[film festival]] held annually in [[Sheffield]], UK. It was the largest festival of its kind in the UK in 2010, screening over 140 films from 14 countries. The festival is run as a collaboration between students at [[University of Sheffield]] and [[Sheffield Hallam University]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.empireonline.com/forum/tm.asp?m=2593843&mpage=1&key=&NID=0#2754569 |title=Sheffield 'No Limits' International Student Film Festival! |publisher=Empireonline.com |date= |accessdate=2012-05-07}}</ref>

The name comes from the festival's 'no limits' policy on submissions. There are no restrictions on length, subject or content of films screened. Additionally, the organisers pledge to screen every film entered.

'The idea is to encourage young and aspiring [[filmmaker]]s to fully explore their creative and artistic potential. Show us what you've got! You don't need to be a film student to enter, just the vision and drive to make a film.'<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nolimitsfilmfestival.com/about.php |title=Film Festival &#124; Cash Advance &#124; Debt Consolidation &#124; Insurance at |publisher=Nolimitsfilmfestival.com |date= |accessdate=2012-05-07}}</ref>

Submissions for the 2011 festival are planned to open on October 1, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vimeo.com/user3034160 |title=No Limits Student Film Festival on Vimeo |publisher=Vimeo.com |date=2011-10-01 |accessdate=2012-05-07}}</ref>

