{{Infobox UN resolution |number = 235 |organ = SC |date = June 9 |year = 1967 |meeting = 1352 |code = |document = https://undocs.org/S/RES/235(1967) |for = 15 |abstention = 0 |against = 0 |subject = The situation in the Middle East |result = Adopted |image = Israel Syria Locator.png |caption = Map highlighting Israel (green) and Syria (orange) }}
'''[[United Nations]] [[List of UN Security Council Resolutions|Security Council Resolution]] 235''', adopted on June 9, 1967, after noting that the governments of both [[Israel]] and [[Syria]] have accepted the Council's demand for a cease-fire, the Council demanded that hostilities should cease forthwith and requested that the [[United Nations Secretary-General|Secretary-General]] make immediate contacts with the Governments of Israel and Syria to immediately arrange compliance with the cease-fire and to report to the Security Council within 2 hours of the resolution.
The meeting, requested by the [[Soviet Union]] and [[United States]], adopted the resolution unanimously. The same day, [[Syria]] and [[Israel]] accepted the terms of the resolution.<ref name="well">{{cite book|last=Wellens|first=Karen|author2=T.M.C. Asser Instituut |title=Resolutions and statements of the United Nations Security Council (1946-1989): a thematic guide|publisher=BRILL|year=1990|page=447|isbn=978-0-7923-0796-9}}</ref>
